<item>
            <title>[FELIX-1942] Component Factory instances are may reactivate</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-1942</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to secion 112.5.5, Factory Component, of the Declarative Services specification, component factory instances are never reactivated:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        Once a component configuration created by the Component Factory has been&lt;br/&gt;
        deactivated, that component configuration will not be reactivated or used again.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently such instances are not really disposed off but just deactivated and may later be reactivated, which is wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
